From Wikipedia:



April Wine is a Canadian rock band formed in 1969. According to the band, they chose the name 'April Wine' simply because members thought the two words sounded good together.[1] The band has released more than 20 albums and continues to attract fans to its concerts, within and without Canada, more than 40 years after its beginning as a hard rock group.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Classic Masters is a compilation album by the Canadian rock band April Wine, released in 2002.[1] The picture on the album cover is a reprint of the albums First Glance (1978) (American version only), The Hits (1987), and Greatest Hits (1979).
